and he hasn‘t joined in.

1983
01:32:33.828 --> 01:32:36.854
I think he‘s hurt.
I think maybe we owe
him an apology.

1984
01:32:36.931 --> 01:32:38.990
What. because
I laughed at him?

1985
01:32:39.968 --> 01:32:41.993
Well. yeah.

1986
01:32:45.173 --> 01:32:46.765
Look. Ginny.

1987
01:32:47.809 --> 01:32:50.937
when people have been
friends as long as we have

1988
01:32:51.012 --> 01:32:52.912
it‘s not
such a terrible thing

1989
01:32:52.981 --> 01:32:55.381
to kid somebody
out of a depression.

1990
01:32:56.317 --> 01:32:59.684
So don‘t get upset
about what you
don‘t understand.

1991
01:33:07.495 --> 01:33:09.793
I’ve just about
had it with you people.

1992
01:33:10.465 --> 01:33:11.796
What‘s the matter?

1993
01:33:12.767 --> 01:33:14.997
I’ll tell you what‘s
the matter. I’m mad.

1994
01:33:15.069 --> 01:33:16.536
(Nick)
Ginny?

1995
01:33:17.071 --> 01:33:18.333
I fall in love
with this man.

1996
01:33:18.406 --> 01:33:20.465
and all of a sudden.
in addition to him

1997
01:33:20.541 --> 01:33:22.941
I’ve got four
constant companions!

1998
01:33:23.244 --> 01:33:25.439
I have to work out
a new relationship

1999
01:33:25.513 --> 01:33:27.276
with somebody who
is going through

2000
01:33:27.348 --> 01:33:29.976
the worst period of his life.
only I can‘t do it alone

2001
01:33:30.051 --> 01:33:32.417
I’ve got to do it in
front of four other people!

2002
01:33:32.487 --> 01:33:35.422
And it‘s not as if
my privacy was invaded.

2003
01:33:35.490 --> 01:33:37.583
you all have let me
know every single day

2004
01:33:37.659 --> 01:33:39.889
that I have been
intruding on your territory!

2005
01:33:43.231 --> 01:33:45.825
Let me tell you something.
As far as I’m concerned

2006
01:33:46.234 --> 01:33:49.431
you‘re all demanding
and unforgiving.
every single one of you.

2007
01:33:49.837 --> 01:33:52.431
Everybody is sweet
and warm and simple

2008
01:33:52.507 --> 01:33:53.940
but everybody ignores me.

2009
01:33:54.008 --> 01:33:55.669
I’m like a leper.

2010
01:33:56.644 --> 01:33:59.442
I’m--I’m a blank spot
where Anne used to be.

2011
01:34:07.021 --> 01:34:09.046
I’m going to go
take a run in the snow.

2012
01:34:12.360 --> 01:34:13.622
[door slams]

2013
01:34:13.895 --> 01:34:16.455
I hope she‘ll be
all right out there.

2014
01:34:19.300 --> 01:34:20.824
Wish I hadn‘t
said that.

2015
01:34:20.969 --> 01:34:22.231
What happened?

2016
01:34:23.271 --> 01:34:25.296
(Nick)
Ginny! Ginny!

2017
01:34:25.606 --> 01:34:26.630
I’m going after her!

2018
01:34:26.708 --> 01:34:27.732
Nick!

2019
01:34:27.976 --> 01:34:29.102
You got a broken ankle.

2020
01:34:29.177 --> 01:34:30.804
She might fall
down in the dark.

2021
01:34:30.878 --> 01:34:33.870
So what? She fell down
in the daylight.
she didn‘t hurt herself.

2022
01:34:33.948 --> 01:34:35.677
In the dark
she might hurt herself.

2023
01:34:35.750 --> 01:34:37.411
Nick. she‘ll be okay.
Rest your foot.

2024
01:34:37.485 --> 01:34:40.249
(Nick)
I’m not going to run the risk
of her falling down out there.

2025
01:34:40.321 --> 01:34:42.414
(Danny)
Why not?
Because she‘s pregnant.

2026
01:34:44.158 --> 01:34:46.126
Because she‘s pregnant?

2027
01:34:47.128 --> 01:34:48.322
Watch this.

2028
01:34:48.396 --> 01:34:50.159
Here‘s some real
heartwarming acceptance.

2029
01:34:50.231 --> 01:34:53.132
You‘re 43 years old.
you‘re going to
start having babies?

2030
01:34:53.568 --> 01:34:55.195
I don‘t believe this.

2031
01:34:55.770 --> 01:34:57.328
I have to check
everything with you?

2032
01:34:57.405 --> 01:35:00.670
As a matter of fact.
I told you I wanted
to start a new family.

2033
01:35:01.075 --> 01:35:02.337
With babies?

2034
01:35:02.844 --> 01:35:04.368
With what? Airedales?

2035
01:35:05.546 --> 01:35:07.207
Look. do what you want.

2036
01:35:07.415 --> 01:35:09.975
Oh. thanks very much.
I really appreciate that.

2037
01:35:10.551 --> 01:35:12.178
Fellows. come on back inside.

2038
01:35:12.253 --> 01:35:13.447
It’s freezing out here.

2039
01:35:13.521 --> 01:35:15.386
Come on. you can‘t go
after her like that.

2040
01:35:15.456 --> 01:35:16.684
Come on.
Come on.

2041
01:35:16.758 --> 01:35:19.556
Nick. please! Come on.

2042
01:35:29.504 --> 01:35:32.098
(Nick)
It’s starting to get bright.
Where the hell is she?

2043
01:35:33.608 --> 01:35:34.973
[sighing]

2044
01:35:35.043 --> 01:35:36.305
You know.

2045
01:35:37.879 --> 01:35:40.439
when she ran out of here
I started to think of

2046
01:35:40.681 --> 01:35:42.979
all the friends
we‘ve had over the years

2047
01:35:43.051 --> 01:35:44.985
who‘ve jogged
out of our lives.

2048
01:35:46.054 --> 01:35:47.885
All the ones who‘ve. uh.

2049
01:35:48.322 --> 01:35:52.190
who‘ve been inconvenient
to stay friendly with
and it scares me.

2050
01:35:55.229 --> 01:35:58.687
They move to another state
or they‘ve gotten a divorce

2051
01:36:00.334 --> 01:36:02.894
or else we‘ve just gotten
friendly enough with them

2052
01:36:02.970 --> 01:36:05.530
to realize they‘re a kind of
a pain in the ass

2053
01:36:05.606 --> 01:36:08.006
and pretty soon we
never see them again.

2054
01:36:09.911 --> 01:36:11.845
I’ll tell you something.
Jack.

2055
01:36:13.314 --> 01:36:15.782
I don‘t want to
be one of two people

2056
01:36:15.850 --> 01:36:18.341
alone in the world
at the end of my life.

2057
01:36:20.721 --> 01:36:22.450
I want to have friends.

2058
01:36:26.027 --> 01:36:27.892
When I get old

2059
01:36:28.930 --> 01:36:31.364
I’d like you all
to still be there.

2060
01:36:39.240 --> 01:36:40.730
Okay?

2061
01:36:41.609 --> 01:36:43.600
Why can‘t we
just let them be?

2062
01:36:45.346 --> 01:36:47.280
In other words.
I’m the problem?

2063
01:36:48.049 --> 01:36:49.380
I have to have
everything my way.

2064
01:36:49.450 --> 01:36:51.748
I’m unforgiving and cold
and judgmental. right?

2065
01:36:51.819 --> 01:36:52.877
Right.

2066
01:36:52.954 --> 01:36:54.046
Right.

2067
01:36:54.122 --> 01:36:55.646
We‘re talking about me?

2068
01:36:55.890 --> 01:36:58.552
Jack. you know
those probing questions

2069
01:36:58.626 --> 01:36:59.923
you ask all the time?

2070
01:36:59.994 --> 01:37:01.518
You‘re the only
one who answers them.

2071
01:37:01.596 --> 01:37:03.461
Everybody dances to your tune!

2072
01:37:03.865 --> 01:37:05.355
That makes me
sound like a tyrant.

2073
01:37:05.433 --> 01:37:06.866
Well. so what?

2074
01:37:06.968 --> 01:37:09.596
I am not a tyrant.
Goddamn it!

2075
01:37:11.606 --> 01:37:13.540
No matter what crap
I get from people.

2076
01:37:13.608 --> 01:37:15.303
all I ever give
back is a smile.

2077
01:37:16.043 --> 01:37:18.068
I never give
a response that‘s anything

2078
01:37:18.146 --> 01:37:21.081
but fair and rational
and cheerful!

2079
01:37:22.183 --> 01:37:23.650
Be careful!
Be careful!

2080
01:37:23.718 --> 01:37:25.845
Why don‘t you
let your anger out
once in a while?

2081
01:37:25.920 --> 01:37:28.388
You want anger?
There! How‘s that?

2082
01:37:28.456 --> 01:37:29.753
[china clanking]

2083
01:37:29.824 --> 01:37:31.223
(Jack)
Is that angry enough for you?

2084
01:37:31.292 --> 01:37:32.691
How about that?

2085
01:37:32.760 --> 01:37:34.352
[clattering]

2086
01:37:34.462 --> 01:37:37.954
Is that angry enough for you?
Now is that angry enough?

2087
01:37:38.032 --> 01:37:39.795
Here. how about this?

2088
01:37:39.867 --> 01:37:41.391
What the hell you doing?

2089
01:37:41.469 --> 01:37:43.403
You know what
I expect from you.

2090
01:37:43.504 --> 01:37:45.472
I expect closeness

2091
01:37:45.540 --> 01:37:48.441
and warmth
and unconditional acceptance.

2092
01:37:48.509 --> 01:37:50.568
And all I get from you
is secretiveness

2093
01:37:50.645 --> 01:37:52.340
and neurosis and a lot of<i>...</i>

2094
01:37:52.413 --> 01:37:54.244
Goddamn it!
Jesus Christ!

2095
01:37:54.315 --> 01:37:55.373
Put it down!

2096
01:37:55.449 --> 01:37:58.247
I’m not paying for this!
This is your expense!

2097
01:37:58.319 --> 01:37:59.980
Yeah. bet your life!

2098
01:38:00.054 --> 01:38:02.614
All right. stop that!
Is that angry
enough for you. huh?

2099
01:38:02.690 --> 01:38:04.715
(Nick)
Stop that!
All right. stop it!

2100
01:38:04.825 --> 01:38:07.157
(Danny)
Stop it! That‘s enough!
That‘s all. stop it!

2101
01:38:07.261 --> 01:38:08.785
Come on! Settle down!

2102
01:38:08.930 --> 01:38:10.397
[all screaming]

2103
01:38:10.464 --> 01:38:12.762
Come here. Sit down.

2104
01:38:12.833 --> 01:38:15.768
Shh. Shh.
Shh. Shh.

2105
01:38:29.050 --> 01:38:31.848
I wonder what other people do
on their vacations?

2106
01:38:35.089 --> 01:38:36.818
Oh. God. I’m sorry.

2107
01:38:39.160 --> 01:38:40.991
Jesus. look what I did.

2108
01:38:41.128 --> 01:38:42.993
So you freaked out a little.

2109
01:38:43.564 --> 01:38:44.895
So what?

2110
01:38:45.833 --> 01:38:47.391
I lost complete
control of myself.

2111
01:38:47.468 --> 01:38:50.130
Jack. nobody cares.

2112
01:38:51.405 --> 01:38:52.895
Hey.
What?

2113
01:38:54.809 --> 01:38:57.573
You‘re not the best
little boy in the world.

2114
01:38:57.945 --> 01:39:01.904
I hate to break this to you.
but you‘re not
the worst little boy. either.

2115
01:39:07.488 --> 01:39:10.389
You know.
sometimes when you say
things like that

2116
01:39:12.460 --> 01:39:14.155
I really hate you.

2117
01:39:14.228 --> 01:39:15.752
[snickering]
Thank you.

2118
01:39:17.131 --> 01:39:19.395
You know.
sometimes I hate you.

2119
01:39:25.106 --> 01:39:26.437
[sniffling]

2120
01:39:28.109 --> 01:39:29.406
Nick. what are you doing?

2121
01:39:29.477 --> 01:39:30.739
I got to go find her.

2122
01:39:30.811 --> 01:39:32.972
Wait a minute.
You stay.

2123
01:39:33.447 --> 01:39:34.505
I’ll go find her.

2124
01:39:34.582 --> 01:39:35.742
No. I can do it.

2125
01:39:35.816 --> 01:39:38.284
Nick. look. please.
I want to.

2126
01:39:39.153 --> 01:39:40.711
Let me go. please.

2127
01:39:42.423 --> 01:39:43.651
Thanks. but I can do it.

2128
01:39:43.724 --> 01:39:44.918
No. I’ll do it.

2129
01:39:45.459 --> 01:39:46.721
No. I’ll do it!

2130
01:39:46.794 --> 01:39:47.988
You sit down
and wait for me.

2131
01:39:48.062 --> 01:39:49.529
I’ll be right back!

2132
01:39:49.597 --> 01:39:51.462
Will you get out of my way?

2133
01:39:51.532 --> 01:39:53.966
Jack! Don‘t be ridiculous!

2134
01:39:54.035 --> 01:39:55.229
He‘s got a broken ankle!

2135
01:39:55.303 --> 01:39:56.600
You‘ve got a torn ligament.

2136
01:39:56.671 --> 01:39:59.003
You guys wouldn‘t get
10 feet in that snow.

2137
01:39:59.073 --> 01:40:00.301
I’d get farther
than he can.

2138
01:40:00.374 --> 01:40:01.705
I’d get farther
than both of you.

2139
01:40:01.776 --> 01:40:04.267
What do you guys think
a pregnant woman is?
An invalid?

2140
01:40:04.378 --> 01:40:05.675
I’ll be back
in two minutes.

2141
01:40:05.746 --> 01:40:07.236
Better start
fixing up this place.

2142
01:40:07.315 --> 01:40:10.011
That moose is going
to cost a fortune.

2143
01:40:15.656 --> 01:40:19.353
(Danny)
Ginny! Don‘t move.
I’ll be right there!

2144
01:40:19.560 --> 01:40:21.152
Stay right there!

2145
01:40:23.998 --> 01:40:25.329
[ice cracking]

2146
01:40:32.073 --> 01:40:33.370
Oh!

2147
01:40:35.609 --> 01:40:37.474
[screaming]

2148
01:40:37.545 --> 01:40:39.877
Hey. wait! Help me!

2149
01:40:40.915 --> 01:40:42.143
Help me!

2150
01:40:42.216 --> 01:40:44.343
Run to the lodge!
Go get help!

2151
01:40:44.418 --> 01:40:45.942
I can‘t get out!

2152
01:40:48.789 --> 01:40:50.950
Run! Go faster. faster!

2153
01:40:52.860 --> 01:40:54.725
Help! Help!

2154
01:41:02.837 --> 01:41:04.236
(Nick)
Are you all right?

2155
01:41:05.806 --> 01:41:08.536
(Ginny)
Danny went through the ice
and he can‘t get out!

2156
01:41:11.512 --> 01:41:13.503
[all clamoring]

2157
01:41:22.356 --> 01:41:24.381
Jack!
Please help.

2158
01:41:50.317 --> 01:41:52.717
Help! Help!

2159
01:42:00.795 --> 01:42:02.126
Quick!

2160
01:42:03.864 --> 01:42:06.059
[all clamoring]

2161
01:42:07.735 --> 01:42:09.896
(Kate)
Jack. don‘t go too far out!

2162
01:42:11.839 --> 01:42:13.966
Okay. Danny!

2163
01:42:14.041 --> 01:42:15.235
Lift up your arms!

2164
01:42:15.309 --> 01:42:16.298
This side.

2165
01:42:16.377 --> 01:42:17.639
(Jack)
Wait a minute.

2166
01:42:17.711 --> 01:42:18.643
Ready here!

2167
01:42:18.712 --> 01:42:20.942
Get your arm around that!
Get it under your elbow!

2168
01:42:21.015 --> 01:42:22.312
God damn it.
lift your arm up!

2169
01:42:22.383 --> 01:42:23.372
Danny. get it around!

2170
01:42:23.451 --> 01:42:24.782
Okay. hold onto the rope.

2171
01:42:24.852 --> 01:42:25.944
I got
the blanket.

2172
01:42:26.020 --> 01:42:27.112
Okay. go!

2173
01:42:27.254 --> 01:42:28.346
(Nick)
Back it up.

2174
01:42:28.622 --> 01:42:30.419
Okay. go back.
Go ahead.

2175
01:42:30.491 --> 01:42:31.515
Go back slowly.

2176
01:42:31.592 --> 01:42:32.581
Easy! Easy! Easy!

2177
01:42:32.660 --> 01:42:33.627
Pull the rope!

2178
01:42:33.694 --> 01:42:34.626
Easy.

2179
01:42:35.029 --> 01:42:36.257
That‘s it. Danny.

2180
01:42:36.397 --> 01:42:38.991
(Jack)
Go on. keep going!

2181
01:42:39.066 --> 01:42:41.000
(Nick)
Keep going!

2182
01:42:41.168 --> 01:42:42.658
All right. hold it!

2183
01:42:46.974 --> 01:42:48.874
Danny!

2184
01:42:48.943 --> 01:42:50.240
Danny!

2185
01:42:50.344 --> 01:42:51.868
Danny?
How is he?

2186
01:42:51.946 --> 01:42:52.878
Danny!

2187
01:42:52.947 --> 01:42:53.914
Don‘t say that!

2188
01:42:53.981 --> 01:42:54.948
Danny?

2189
01:42:56.517 --> 01:42:57.779
Danny?

2190
01:42:57.852 --> 01:42:59.183
Breathe. honey!

2191
01:42:59.253 --> 01:43:01.414
(Jack)
Little more!
Rub--rub his legs.

2192
01:43:01.489 --> 01:43:04.014
Come on.
Come on. sweetheart.

2193
01:43:06.660 --> 01:43:08.321
[retching]

2194
01:43:10.798 --> 01:43:12.231
Thank God!

2195
01:43:14.168 --> 01:43:16.033
Danny. are you all right?

2196
01:43:16.103 --> 01:43:17.934
Are you all right.
honey?

2197
01:43:18.272 --> 01:43:19.864
(Nick)
You almost drowned.

2198
01:43:20.875 --> 01:43:22.206
Keep covered up.

2199
01:43:22.276 --> 01:43:25.177
Thanks. I’m okay.
I’m okay. Thank you.

2200
01:43:25.246 --> 01:43:27.237
I almost died. and thank you.

2201
01:43:27.314 --> 01:43:28.975
(Nick)
Get him up!

2202
01:43:29.083 --> 01:43:31.074
[ice cracking]

2203
01:43:31.151 --> 01:43:32.812
[screaming]

2204
01:43:35.689 --> 01:43:39.090
Oh. my God! My Mercedes!

2205
01:43:40.227 --> 01:43:42.491
[Danny screaming]

2206
01:43:46.800 --> 01:43:48.563
[water bubbling]

2207
01:43:49.203 --> 01:43:52.900
How could you drive
my Mercedes on thin ice?

2208
01:43:52.973 --> 01:43:54.065
Oh!

2209
01:43:55.543 --> 01:43:56.840
(Nick)
Danny. come on. get up.

2210
01:43:56.911 --> 01:43:58.173
(Ginny)
Come on.

2211
01:44:01.448 --> 01:44:02.506
Oh. God!

2212
01:44:02.583 --> 01:44:03.914
Get off
the blanket.

2213
01:44:04.585 --> 01:44:06.485
It was brand new!

2214
01:44:06.754 --> 01:44:09.484
In three years.
I could have gotten
twice what I paid for it!

2215
01:44:09.557 --> 01:44:12.321
Danny. Danny. we‘ll get
someone to fish it out
for you.

2216
01:44:12.393 --> 01:44:15.419
What the hell am I going to do
with a rusty Mercedes?

2217
01:44:15.496 --> 01:44:16.622
It’s gone!

2218
01:44:16.697 --> 01:44:17.789
It’s gone.

2219
01:44:17.865 --> 01:44:19.765
It sank like a stone.

2220
01:44:19.833 --> 01:44:20.993
(Claudia)
Danny!

2221
01:44:21.068 --> 01:44:23.866
You are alive.
You have your life.

2222
01:44:24.038 --> 01:44:26.734
You have us and we love you.
so shut up!

2223
01:44:26.807 --> 01:44:27.865
Come on. Dan.

2224
01:44:27.942 --> 01:44:29.603
Go in. You‘re going to
freeze to death.

2225
01:44:29.677 --> 01:44:31.702
Get into
the lodge and get warm.

2226
01:44:32.246 --> 01:44:33.838
Sorry.
I just got a little crazy.

2227
01:44:33.914 --> 01:44:36.883
I’m sorry.
What do I care about the car.

2228
01:44:36.984 --> 01:44:38.417
It’s you I care about.

2229
01:44:38.485 --> 01:44:40.112
(Nick)
Let‘s go! Come on!

2230
01:44:40.187 --> 01:44:42.121
To hell with the car.
thank you.

2231
01:44:43.123 --> 01:44:46.058
Oh. my God.
you sank my car!

2232
01:44:46.126 --> 01:44:47.286
Get back.

